#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:1
msgid "GitHub Actions integration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:3
msgid ""
"You can use _Black_ within a GitHub Actions workflow without setting your "
"own Python environment. Great for enforcing that your code matches the "
"_Black_ code style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:6
msgid "Compatibility"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:8
msgid ""
"This action is known to support all GitHub-hosted runner OSes. In addition, "
"only published versions of _Black_ are supported (i.e. whatever is available "
"on PyPI)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:11
msgid ""
"Finally, this action installs _Black_ with the `colorama` extra so the `--"
"color` flag should work fine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:14
msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:16
msgid ""
"Create a file named `.github/workflows/black.yml` inside your repository "
"with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:18
msgid ""
"name: Lint\n"
"\n"
"on: [push, pull_request]\n"
"\n"
"jobs:\n"
"  lint:\n"
"    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n"
"    steps:\n"
"      - uses: actions/checkout@v6\n"
"      - uses: psf/black@stable\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:31
msgid ""
"We recommend the use of the `@stable` tag, but per version tags also exist "
"if you prefer that. Note that the action's version you select is independent "
"of the version of _Black_ the action will use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:35
msgid "Versions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:37
msgid ""
"The version of _Black_ the action will use can be configured via `version` "
"or read from the `pyproject.toml` file. The action defaults to the latest "
"release available on PyPI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:40
msgid ""
"`version` can be any [valid version specifier](https://packaging.python.org/"
"en/latest/glossary/#term-Version-Specifier) or just the version number if "
"you want an exact version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:44
msgid ""
"If you want to match versions covered by Black's [stability policy](labels/"
"stability-policy), you can use the compatible release operator (`~=`):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:48
msgid ""
"- uses: psf/black@stable\n"
"  with:\n"
"    options: \"--check --verbose\"\n"
"    src: \"./src\"\n"
"    version: \"~= 26.0\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:56
msgid ""
"To read the version from the `pyproject.toml` file instead, set "
"`use_pyproject` to `true`. This will first look into the `tool.black."
"required-version` field, then the `dependency-groups` table, then the "
"`project.dependencies` array and finally the `project.optional-dependencies` "
"table. Note that this requires Python >= 3.11, so using the setup-python "
"action may be required, for example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:62
msgid ""
"**Security note:** `use_pyproject` only accepts standard version specifiers "
"for `black` (for example `==`, `~=`, `>=` and ranges like `>=25,<26`). "
"Direct references such as `black @ https://...` are not supported. If your "
"workflow runs on untrusted pull requests (for example from forks), prefer "
"setting `with.version` explicitly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:67
msgid ""
"- uses: actions/setup-python@v6\n"
"  with:\n"
"    python-version: \"3.13\"\n"
"- uses: psf/black@stable\n"
"  with:\n"
"    options: \"--check --verbose\"\n"
"    src: \"./src\"\n"
"    use_pyproject: true\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:78
msgid ""
"Only versions available from PyPI are supported, so no commit SHAs or branch "
"names."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:80
msgid "Jupyter Notebooks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:82
msgid ""
"If you want to include Jupyter Notebooks, it can be enabled by setting "
"`jupyter` to `true` (default is `false`):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:85
msgid ""
"- uses: psf/black@stable\n"
"  with:\n"
"    jupyter: true\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:91
msgid ""
"See the [Jupyter Notebooks guide](../guides/"
"using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md) for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:94
msgid "CLI Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:96
msgid ""
"You can also configure the arguments passed to _Black_ via `options` "
"(defaults to `'--check --diff'`) and `src` (default is `'.'`). Please note "
"that the [`--check` flag](labels/exit-code) is required so that the workflow "
"fails if _Black_ finds files that need to be formatted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:101
msgid "Here's an example configuration:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/github_actions.md:103
msgid ""
"- uses: psf/black@stable\n"
"  with:\n"
"    options: \"--check --verbose\"\n"
"    src: \"./src\"\n"
"    jupyter: true\n"
"    version: \"21.5b1\"\n"
msgstr ""
